Author: xiaoyingdou
Text: I can sympathise so much, my closest friend told me she was told at the doctors that she was at high risk of developing anorexia and because we're minors she had to get treatment. it just made me feel insignificant, as if I hadn't starved myself enough to be worthy of any help, and I still feel like this today. she's fine now and so supportive of me, she's the only person I've told, and I am so grateful for her. :'( I just hate always feeling like I don't deserve help.

Author: raverae
Text: Everybody is different. Just bc she Almost died doesn’t mean what you’re doing isn’t doing your body any harm. I know it’s easier said than done but why not try eating healthy foods like fruits and vegetables? Focus on nourishing your body . It’s a Deeper issue you’re having . Maybe see a therapist.
